12-0675-2\" target=\"_blank\">The Oxford Principles</a>,&quot; a draft code of conduct for geoengineering research. It calls for geoengineering to be regulated as a public good, for public participation in decision-making and for disclosure of research and open publication of results.</p><p>In addition to his work at Oxford, Kruger is also CEO of Origen Power, which is developing <a href=\"http://www.origenpower.com/\" target=\"_blank\">a process</a> that uses natural gas to generate electricity in a way that removes carbon dioxide from the atmosphere.</p>"}],"url":"https://www.ted.com/talks/tim_kruger_can_we_stop_climate_change_by_removing_co2_from_the_air","viewed_count":1170289,"talks":[{"recommendations":{"status":"approved","headline":"Tim Kruger recommends","blurb":"More resources about geoengineering, curated by Tim Kruger","start_at":null,"end_at":null,"published":true,"eyebrow":"Tim Kruger recommends","type":"recommendation","rec_lists":[{"title":"","description":"","rec_items":[{"label":"READ_Article","headline":"\"Emissions reduction: Scrutinize CO2 removal methods\"","blurb":"A commentary by Phil Williamson explaining both the need for, and the issues with, the large-scale removal of carbon dioxide from the air. ","note":"Phil Williamson\r\n*Nature*, 2016","link_url":"https://www.nature.com/news/emissions-reduction-scrutinize-co2-removal-methods-1.19318","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Article","headline":"\"Abandon hype in climate models\"","blurb":"An article in *The Guardian& that I wrote with Oliver Geden and Steve Rayner about the dangers of including techniques that remove carbon dioxide from the air in climate models without a sufficient evidence base.","note":"Tim Kruger, Oliver Geden and Steve Rayner\r\n*The Guardian*, 2016","link_url":"https://www.theguardian.com/science/political-science/2016/apr/26/abandon-hype-in-climate-models","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Article","headline":"\"Hal